Package: autotesteR
Title: Automated Functions for Basic Statistical Tests
Version: 0.1.5
Authors@R: 
    person("Luiz", "Garcia", email = "luiz.cardoso@ufpr.br", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The package autotesteR provides simple and intuitive functions 
    to select, apply, and visualize basic statistical tests based on data 
    characteristics. Includes automated checking for normality, homogeneity, 
    and variable types. Statistical methods implemented follow classical 
    references, such as Student (1908) <doi:10.1098/rsta.1908.0018> for the 
    t-test, Mann and Whitney (1947) <doi:10.1214/aoms/1177730491> for the 
    Mann-Whitney U test, Pearson (1896) <doi:10.1080/14786449608620976> for 
    correlation, Spearman (1904) <doi:10.2307/1412159> for rank correlation, 
    Fisher (1925, ISBN:978-0028447308) for ANOVA and chi-square tests.
